node.text: Here’s the raw video of today, Cleck was super in the Clear Round Student Showjumping!! Since our second show day got canceled due too the bad weather here in England we decided to join the clear round SJ (1.10m) which was such good practice and great for our confidence as there wasn’t any show pressure 😂 I had so much fun jumping around the course, Cleck felt super just sadly had one pole, being the first part of the combination which I got a little long to ☺️ Super happy with how my boy jumped this weekend!! Thank you for all your help & support again today @emilyyy.eventing_ 😘

node.text:
This is going to be a longer one… First 2 International Shows in the bag!!🌟🇩🇪 

The past few weeks have been absolutely incredible, jumping the CSI Bronze & Silver Tour at @davidbroomeeventcentre , as well as the 1* Tour at @bolesworthint ☺️ Clecky has been feeling super, jumping me lots of double clears, 2 international placings and a super round in our first 1m15 this year 🥰 He always gives me the best feeling - I owe him so much 🚀🌎

We are currently at @hicksteadevents 2 week BS Tour, where Cleck jumped a lovely double clear and was placed with over 150 starters yesterday - looking forward to another busy week of showjumping ahead 🥰 

A massive thank you to @rayardshowjumping / @emilyjbrooker / @gregoryhillshowjumping for all these incredible opportunities, the continuous support and belief, definitely a summer I won’t forget ☀️ 

#horses #horsesofinstagram #showjumping #showjumper #holsteiner

Im really sorry for being so inactive on here… life & work is keeping me very busy… too busy 😂 But Cleck finished Bicton 2 Week BS Tour on a high, jumping 7/8 clears, with 6 placings and a win!☺️💓 Couldn’t be happier, he’s feeling so great at the moment, preparations for our next show have been on going, we are heading off to Keysoe tomorrow, for another exciting 3 days of showjumping!! Im loving the summer season, there’s a few more weeks of very exciting shows coming up together with @rayardshowjumping / @gregoryhillshowjumping ✨ Thank you for all your help and support, so very grateful to be part of the team 💛 

#horses #horse

Hickstead Al Shira’aa National Championships - and that’s a wrap… 4 incredible days of showjumping coming to an end. Jumping here has been a dream of mine since I was little, a massive thank you to @rayardshowjumping and the entire team, whom without this wouldn’t have been possible, so grateful!! 💕

Cleck completely blew me away jumping DC in 2/3 strong Hickstead Qualifiers, placing with over 200 starters as well as jumping on grass for the first time together 🥺 We had so much fun and it’s safe to say that Hickstead is my new favourite show venue. It was lovely meeting a few of you guys, don’t be afraid to come up to Cleck and I when you spot us, we love meeting you all 💛 A few well deserved days off for the best boy, while I catch up with work 😂 

Cleck and I are both fully kitted out by @mybreeches 🛍
